1. COMPETENCY OVERVIEW
==================================================
 
Competency:        Keep It Alive — 会話をつなげよう
Level:             Super Beginner (Pre-A1 → A1)
Weeks:             9–16 (within the student's personal counter)
Total prompts:     224 (56 per purpose)
Delivery method:   Daily LINE message, personal student timetable
 
CORE SKILL:
Reacting naturally and asking follow-up questions — the skills that
prevent awkward silence and make the other person feel genuinely heard.
 
THE C2 PROBLEM — WHY THIS MATTERS:
C1 taught students how to open a conversation. C2 solves what happens
next. The most common failure mode at Super Beginner level is not the
opening — it is the response to what the other person says. Students
frequently:
- Say "I see." or "Oh." and let the silence grow
- Give a flat acknowledgement with no follow-up question
- Answer the original question but ignore the other person's reply
- Miss conversational cues that invite them to keep talking
 
C2 breaks this pattern by training two things in sequence:
1. React with emotion first ("Oh really?!" / "No way!" / "That's great!")
2. Ask a specific follow-up question immediately after
 
This two-part pattern — react then ask — is the engine of natural
English conversation at every level.
 
STUDENT PROFILE AT THIS LEVEL (entering C2):
- Has completed 8 weeks of C1 (First Contact)
- Can open a conversation and give a basic answer
- Knows how to ask one question back ("How about you?")
- Still freezes when the other person says something unexpected
- Still gives flat responses ("I see." / "That's good.") to real news
- Expected response at C2 entry: 1–2 sentences
- Expected response at C2 completion: 2–3 sentences with a follow-up
 
JAPANESE SUPPORT LEVEL: High (●●●●○)
Includes: vocabulary translations, grammar explanations, cultural context,
closing achievement checklist (Week 16 Day 7 only).
Does NOT include: pronunciation tips, opening goal summary.
(Pronunciation tips were present in C1 Full support. C2 students have
completed 8 weeks and have an established phonological base. Opening goal
summaries are removed — C2 students already understand the system format.
However, the closing achievement checklist IS retained: seeing a concrete
list of skills earned after 8 weeks of effort provides genuine motivation
and reinforces progress, regardless of which competency the student is in.)
 
COMPETENCY GOAL (not stated to student in Week 9 — conveyed through
progress and achievement at Week 16):
By Week 16, students will be able to:
- React naturally to what someone says ("Oh really?!" / "No way!")
- Ask a meaningful follow-up question ("What happened?" / "How did it go?")
- Show genuine interest and keep the other person talking
- Have a flowing 5–7 line conversation without awkward silences
 
 
