KEY CONTRAST: C2 vs C1 at the sentence level
---------------------------------------------
C1 pattern (learned):
  A: "How's your day?"
  B: "Pretty good! I just finished a big meeting. How about you?"
 
C2 pattern (new at C2):
  A: "I just finished a really tough presentation!"
  B: "Oh wow, seriously?! How did it go?"  ← C2 skill being built
 
The difference is that in C2 the student must react to WHAT THE OTHER
PERSON SAID, not just answer a question. This requires listening and
producing a response at the same time — a significant cognitive step
up from C1.
 
 
